      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</b>\n</p><p><b>José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</b>,<br />\na Brazilian mathematician and historian of mathematics with interests in computer science, chess and computer chess. \nHe contributed to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Krabb%C3%A9\">Tim Krabbé's</a> chess records <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>, \n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter's</a> Chess Seesaw <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, \nand is mentioned on various sites related to puzzles <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and mathematics. José was frequent poster in <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a> in the early 2000s with focus on <a href=\"/Test-Positions\" title=\"Test-Positions\">test-positions</a> and <a href=\"/Chess_Problems,_Compositions_and_Studies\" title=\"Chess Problems, Compositions and Studies\">studies</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#2000\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2001\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2001</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2002_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2002 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000\">2000</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 2000\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=92283\">Pawn endings [blocked pawns</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 26, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=99672\">OSTRICH-KAISSA, Stockholm 1974</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 01, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/WCCC_1974\" title=\"WCCC 1974\">WCCC 1974</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=101063\">\"The Tale of a Small Tree\" by M.M.Botvinnik [fragment</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 09, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Mikhail_Botvinnik\" title=\"Mikhail Botvinnik\">Mikhail Botvinnik</a>, <a href=\"/R%C3%A9ti_Endgame_Study\" title=\"Réti Endgame Study\">Réti Endgame Study</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=101232\">\"A fantastic mate in seven\"</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 10, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=101714\">Test position:Colle-O´Hanlon;Nice,1930 [13...Kg6 or 13...Kg8</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 13, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=103584\">Off-topic:How Long Before Superintelligence?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 27, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=107742\">Deception and Enchantment in the Life of the Automaton Chess Player</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 25, 2000 <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=108799\">\"Techmate\" by Garry Kasparov</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 02, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Kasparov_versus_Deep_Blue_1997\" title=\"Kasparov versus Deep Blue 1997\">Kasparov versus Deep Blue 1997</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=133725\">Sidney Samole (1935-2000)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 18, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Sidney_Samole\" title=\"Sidney Samole\">Sidney Samole</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=134782\">Schach 2.7 vs Cray Blitz [1986 World Computer Chess Championship</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 24, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/WCCC_1986#Adjudication\" title=\"WCCC 1986\">WCCC 1986 Adjudication</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=137268\">Dark Thought-IM Johan van Mil [2406</a> * 12st AEGON, Round 5 April 22, 1997] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 24, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Aegon_1997\" title=\"Aegon 1997\">Aegon 1997</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2001\">2001</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2001\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=152066\">Twin miniatures [by Werner Speckmann,1955</a> Mate in 17 and Mate in 13] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 26, 2001</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=160748\">KBNKP [a miniature study,mate in 34</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 29, 2001</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=186117\">Cray Blitz vs Belle [1981 North American Computer Chess Championship</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 29, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/ACM_1981\" title=\"ACM 1981\">ACM 1981</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2002_...\">2002 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2002 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=210702\">Crafty-IsiChess,CCT4,r11 ==&gt; A move to avoid?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 29, 2002&#160;» <a href=\"/CCT4\" title=\"CCT4\">CCT4</a>, <a href=\"/Zugzwang\" title=\"Zugzwang\">Zugzwang</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=347351\">Test Position = Study by David Przepiorka [Vorwärts, 1910</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 05, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=361952\">Test Position = Ruffian vs Shredder = Leiden 2004 [Round 7</a> 23. Qxb4?] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 27, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/ICT_2004\" title=\"ICT 2004\">ICT 2004</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=379472\">Bilbao = I Mundial de Personas contra Ordenadores</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 28, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Man_vs_Machine_Team_Championship\" title=\"Man vs Machine Team Championship\">Man vs Machine Team Championship</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=386936\">Test Position = GM Tony Miles vs Deep Thought, 1989 [14...Bxh2!!</a>] by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 09, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Deep_Thought\" title=\"Deep Thought\">Deep Thought</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=422970\">Kasparov [HBR interview]&#160;: 'IBM committed a crime against science.'</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">José Antônio Fabiano Mendes</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 26, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/Deep_Blue\" title=\"Deep Blue\">Deep Blue</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/seesaw.html\">The Chess Seesaw</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.datacomm.ch/t_wolf/tw/misc/squares.html\">The 70*70 Square Puzzle</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.datacomm.ch/t_wolf/\">Thomas Wolf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Backtracking\" title=\"Backtracking\">Backtracking</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/pythagoras/herons2.shtml\">A Proof of the Pythagorean Theorem From Heron's Formula II</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/index.shtml\">Alexander Bogomolny</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/manifesto/index.shtml\">Cut the Knot</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/do_you_know/GoldenRatio.shtml\">Golden Ratio in Geometry</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/manifesto/index.shtml\">Cut the Knot</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cut-the-knot.org/wiki-math/index.php?n=Algebra.ProductOfFourConsecutiveIntegers\">CTK Wiki Math - Algebra - Product of Four Consecutive Integers</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jos%C3%A9_Ant%C3%B4nio_Fabiano_Mendes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Krabb%C3%A9\">Tim Krabbé's</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://timkr.home.xs4all.nl/records/recordstxt.htm\">Chess records</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/seesaw.html\">The Chess Seesaw</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.datacomm.ch/t_wolf/tw/misc/squares.html\">The 70*70 Square Puzzle</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.datacomm.ch/t_wolf/\">Thomas Wolf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Backtracking\" title=\"Backtracking\">Backtracking</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Mikhail_Botvinnik\" title=\"Mikhail Botvinnik\">Mikhail Botvinnik</a> (<b>1993</b>). <i>Three Positions</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#16_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 16, No. 2</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maelzel%27s_Chess_Player\">Maelzel's Chess Player from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.forbes.com/asap/1999/0222/071.html\">Techmate</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garry_Kasparov\">Garry Kasparov</a>, February 22, 1999, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forbes\">Forbes.com</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hbr.org/2005/04/strategic-intensity/ar/1\">Strategic Intensity - A Conversation with World Chess Champion  Garry Kasparov</a> by <a rel=\"